High Level Design

-> High level design or HLD is an intial step in the development of applications in which the overall structure of the system 
is planned. Mainly focuses on different components of the system work together without getting to know the internal code and 
implementation.  
-> Helps everyone in the project understand the requirements and ensures good communication during development.
-> Crucial for developers, architects and product managers because it allows them to make sure that all stakeholders
are align with the project objectives. Thats why it is called as Macro level design.

The most common request flow most applications follow from user to data and back.     ->1.1 data stores
