                                                                  2. Identity/ access   -> 1.3 Asunc Queue & Workers 

Components of High level design:
================================
Understanding the components of high level design is inportant becauses that meets user needs and technical requirements.

1. System Architecture -> System architecture is an overview of the system that represents the structure and relationship between other components.
It helps to visually represent how different parts interact and function.

2. Modeuls and components -> High level design breaks down the system into modules or components each with specific roles and reponsibilities, 
and has distinct function that contributes to the entire system, helping in developing an efficient system.

3. Data Flow Diagrams -> Data flow diagrams demonstrate the data movement within the system.They help to understand how the
information is processed and pass from one end to other.

4. Interface design -> It includes the design of application programming interface (apis) for system integration and user interfaces (UIs) for 
user interation, ensuring seemless functionality and communication between components.

5. Technology stack -> The technology stack includes various technologies and tools usind in the system includes databases,
framweworks and programming languages.

6. Deployment architecture -> It includes how the system will be hosted and accessed.It includes server configurations,
cloud infrastructure and network considerations.

