Purpose and characteristics of HLD
====================================

-> The purpose of High level design(HLD) is to add necessary detailed description to represent a suitable model.This is designed to help with 
operational requirements and how the modules interact. Basically, HLD is a technical representation of functional requirements and how the
data flow across components.

-> characteristics of HLD:
1. A diagram representing each designed aspect is included in the HLD ( which is based on requirements and anticipated results).
2. Description of hardware (database, load balance, cloud servers) , software  ( frontend, backend) and user interfaces.
3. The workflow of the user's typical process is detailed, along with performance specifications.

